<F P=100> REGIONAL ECONOMIC STATISTICAL COMMUNIQUES </F>
<H3> <TI>   Henan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Henan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2004083894 Zhengzhou HENAN RIBAO in Chinese 26 Feb 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> HK2004083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zhengzhou HENAN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Henan Provincial Statistics </F>
Bureau; date not given: "Statistical Report Issued by Henan 
Provincial Statistics Bureau on National Economic and Social 
Development in 1993"] 
  [Text] In 1993, led by the provincial party and 
government, Henan people seized the opportunity, deepened 
reforms, and increased the pace of the building a socialist 
market economic system and scored positive results in 
implementing the Central Committee's and State Council's 
policies of strengthening and improving macroregulation and 
control. The province's economy maintained the good momentum of 
relatively fast development. Urban and rural residents' income 
increased, and their living standards rose. Social projects 
progressed faster; preliminary statistics indicated that the 
province's GDP in 1993 was 158.029 billion yuan, up 15.7 percent 
from last year. Of this total, the growth value of secondary 
industry was 76.618 billion yuan, up 21.5 percent; and 40.414 
billion yuan for tertiary industry, up 11.5 percent. However, in 
economic operations, problems remained, such as relatively 
inadequate input into agriculture and infrastructure; production 
and operations at some enterprises were not good and their 
economic returns were far from ideal; and there was a greater 
likelihood of latent inflation. It still requires arduous 
effort to maintain the sustained, rapid, and healthy development 
of the province's economy. 
<H5>  I. Agriculture </H5>
  In 1993 the province paid greater attention to the status of 
agriculture as the basis of the province's economy and further 
induced peasants' production activity by market-oriented 
efforts. This, plus relatively good weather, resulted in good 
harvests in agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry, and 
fishery. The growth value for the province's primary industry 
hit 40.997 billion yuan, up 10.4 percent. 
  Among the main farm produce, the total output of grains and 
oil-bearing crops rose to record high levels; that of fruits and 
flax rose considerably, but tobacco output went down quite 
considerably. 


