  Industrial economic performance was greatly improved. 
According to statistics by independent accounting industrial 
enterprises in the whole region, income from product sales added 
up to 10.66 billion yuan, an increase of 55 percent over the 
previous year; the total amount of profits and taxes reached 980 
million yuan, an increase of 54.7 percent; the total amount of 
profits with losses deducted was 180 million yuan, an increase 
of 135 percent; and the composite economic performance index was 
76.6 percent, an increase of 10 percentage points over those of 
the previous year. Of the six factors that made up the 
composite economic performance index, the production and sales 
rate reached 97.6 percent, an increase of 2.2 percentage points; 
the profits and tax rate of funds was 6.5 percent, an increase 
of 1.5 percentage points over 1992; the cost and expense profit 
rate was 1.9 percent, an increase of 0.6 percentage points; 
labor productivity was 10,688 yuan per person, an increase of 
30.2 percent; the floating funds turnover rate was 1.4 times, an 
increase of 0.1 times; and the added value rate was 31.4 
percent, dropping by 1.7 percentage points. But the overall 
industrial economic performance remained low, and quite a large 
number of enterprises were still losing money. 
  The production situation of building enterprises took a 
favorable turn in 1993. With the high-speed growth of fixed 
asset investments and constant in-depth reforms of building 
enterprises, state-owned building enterprises fulfilled a total 
annual output of 1.06 billion yuan, an increase of 32 percent 
over the previous year. All-member labor productivity 
calculated by total output was 22,999 yuan per person, an 
increase of 39.4 percent over 1992. Area under construction in 
the whole year totalled 1.758 million square meters, up 25 
percent, of which the area completed totalled 740,000 square 
meters, even 5with that of the previous year. Among 1,567 
projects under construction in the whole year, 1,365 projects 
carried out the contract-based responsibility system, accounting 
for 87 percent. Enterprise economic performance took a further 
turn for the better. 
<H5>  III. Fixed Asset Investment </H5>
  Fixed asset investment grew by a big margin, and 
preferential 
measures were taken for investments in capital construction and 
technological transformation projects. All-society fixed asset 
investments reached 5.16 billion yuan, an increase of 35.5 
percent, and was the third highest growth year since reform and 
opening-up began. In these investments, central authorities 
projects reached 1.79 billion yuan, an increase of 54.7 percent; 
and local projects reached 3.37 billion yuan, an increase of 
27.1 percent. There was overall growth of various economic 
investments, of which state-owned units reached an investment 
level of 4.14 billion yuan, up 35 percent; and collective units 
reached 610 million yuan, up 103 percent. In state-owned unit 
investments, capital construction investments amounted to 2.59 
billion yuan, an increase of 31.8 percent; renovation and 
transformation investments amounted to 1.12 billion yuan, an 
increase of 40.2 percent; and commodity residential flat 
investments amounted to 260 million yuan, an increase of 65 
percent. Capital construction investments based on trades were: 
Agricultural investment reached 148 million yuan, even with that 
of the previous year; industrial investments reached 910 million 
yuan, up 10.6 percent (energy investments reached 680 million 
yuan, up 44.7 percent, accounting for 26.3 percent of capital 
construction investments); investments in commerce and food and 
drinks business totalled 204 million yuan, an increase of 94 
percent; real estate investment amounted to 69 million yuan, up 
25 percent; culture, education, and public health amounted to 96 
million yuan, up 7.8 percent; scientific research amounted to 11 
million yuan, up by 83 percent; and investments in 
communications, post, and telecommunications amounted to 960 
million yuan, an increase of 81 percent, accounting for 37 
percent of capital construction investments. 
  Major construction and large and medium-sized construction 
projects made new achievements. The Baoji-Zhongwei Railway 
reached an investment of over 600 million yuan, and tracks were 
laid from Zhongwei to Guyuan; the phase-five extension project 
of the Shizuishan Power Plant was completed; construction of 
three coal mine areas of Lingwu, Shizuishan, and Shitanjing was 
in full swing; construction on the Yanhuanding Pumping Project, 
Yin-Gu Highway, and Yinchuan Yellow River Bridge was drawing to 
an end; and the early-stage preparatory work of the construction 
of Yinchuan Hedong Airport was under way. The preparations for 
the phase-two project of the Daba Power Plant were completed, 
and work can start officially in 1994. The Northwest Ball 
Bearing Factory, Yinchuan Rubber Factory, Ningxia Cement 
Factory, and other major technological transformation projects 
were going smoothly. 
  Construction projects were relatively concentrated. There 
were 1,220 capital construction and technological transformation 
projects of state-owned units, a reduction of 194 projects from 
those of the previous year, and among them, 780 projects were 
newly started, a reduction of 229 projects. In 1993 there were 
384 capital construction projects and 320 renovation and 
transformation projects of state-owned units completed and put 
into operation in the whole region. The area of houses under 
construction in the whole society totalled 7.05 million square 
meters, and the area of houses completed totalled 5.41 million 
square meters, with a project completion rate of 76.7 percent, 
in which the area of residential flats completed totalled 4.09 
million square meters. 
<H5>  IV. Communications, Post, and Telecommunications </H5>
  In 1993, communications, post, and telecommunications 
undertakings in the whole region made rapid development as a 
result of continued preferential policies, an increase in input, 
a quickening of the construction of railway, highway, post, and 
telecommunications infrastructure, an increase in airlines and 
flights, and a heightening of the equipment level of post and 
telecommunications offices. The added value realized in the 
whole year totalled 610 million yuan, an increase of 7.8 percent 
over the previous year. 


