  Trees were planted over a total area of 374,000 hectares in 
the province, slightly less than in the previous year, and the 
structure of forestry production was further readjusted, the 
quality was improved, the area of economic forests and forests 
for engineering purposes clearly expanded, and the output of 
forest products increased comprehensively. 
  Animal husbandry production developed steadily and the 
production level rose. The increase in output of major 
livestock products such as meat, eggs, and milk was as follows: 


