<H3> <TI>   Finance Ministry To Liberalize Banking Rules </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Ministry To Liberalize Banking Rules </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2506144194 Taipei CNA in English 1324 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2506144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Danielle Yang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, June 25 (CNA) -- The Finance Ministry has 
decided to allow Taiwan banks easier access in doing business 
with mainland Chinese banks, a ministry official said Saturday 
[25 June]. Under the new measure, Taiwan banks' overseas 
branches will be allowed to do business directly with Mainland 
China's overseas branches, and will no longer have to go through 
foreign banks' overseas branches, the official said. 
  Overseas branches of Taiwan banks can also do business 
directly with foreign banks' mainland branches. 
  Previously, Taiwan banks wishing to do business with 
mainland 
banks had to first go through foreign banks' overseas branches 
and then through foreign banks' mainland branches. 
  The Finance Ministry is expected to submit the new measure 
during a meeting on July 4, the official said. 

</TEXT>

