<F P=106> [By Danielle Yang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, June 25 (CNA) -- Official diplomatic ties 
between the Republic of China [ROC] and South Africa remain 
solid, South African Ambassador J.L. Viljoen said Saturday [25 
June]. Viljoen made the remarks while answering questions from 
the media at a banquet honoring foreign envoys in Taipei. The 
banquet was hosted by the Legislative Yuan's Foreign Affairs 
Committee. 
  Viljoen said South Africa, after it regains membership to 
the 
United Nations, hopes to play a more active and positive role in 
African affairs. He said he had no information on whether 
Pretoria will establish ties with Beijing. Viljoen said his 
government fully understands the efforts the ROC is making to 
enter the United Nations, and said the most urgent task for the 
ROC is to strive for more international support. 
  South Africa has not yet decided on how best to support the 
ROC in its bid to join the United Nations, he added. 

