<F P=102>   SK2506021394 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 0000 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2506021394 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Headed by First Deputy Prime Minister Dostiyev, a 
16-member Supreme Soviet delegation from the Republic of 
Tajikstan arrived in Harbin from Beijing by plane on the evening 
of 23 June to begin its two-day visit in our province. 
  Qi Guiyuan, vice chairman of the provincial people's 
congress standing committee, and Secretary General Liu Tongnian, 
welcomed the delegation at the airport. 
  First Vice Chairman Dostiyev and his entourage was invited 
by 
the standing committee of the National People's Congress [NPC] 
to visit China on 21 June. This is the Tajik legislative 
Assembly's first visit to China. During its stopover in our 
province, the delegation will pay an official visit to the 
provincial people's congress standing committee and visit 
enterprises and plants in Harbin city. 
  Li Yongtai, member of the NPC standing committee, who 
accompanied the delegation during the visit, also arrived in 
Harbin in the same plane. 

