<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Poor Management' Cited for Factory Explosion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Poor Management' Cited for Factory Explosion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2606064994 Beijing CHINA DAILY in English 25 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> HK2606064994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing CHINA DAILY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Cao Min: "Five Die In Glue Factory Explosion"] </F>
  [Text] Five workers were killed and another two seriously 
injured by an explosion at a joint venture in eastern Beijing's 
Tongxian County last Tuesday morning. 
  The blast wrecked the Hong Kong-invested Huaxin Chemical 
Company Ltd factory at 7:45 am while the seven people were 
mixing a solvent adhesive in the workshop, according to Yang 
Wanlu, an official from Beijing's Municipal Labour Bureau. 
  "One of the reasons for the accident was the joint venture's 
poor management and improper operation," said Yang. 
  Since June last year, a number of major industrial accidents 
with fatalities have hit the headlines, particularly from the 
southern coastal areas. Many of the disasters have been 
attributed to slack management and lax safety procedures. 

</TEXT>

