<H3> <TI>   Hu Jintao Ends Inspection of Tianjin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hu Jintao Ends Inspection of Tianjin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2506143094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1334 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2506143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, June 25 (XINHUA) -- Hu Jintao, a senior 
Chinese Communist Party leader, today ended a six-day tour of 
the north China port city of Tianjin and its environs. 
  Hu is a member of the Standing Committee of the Political 
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China 
(CPC) and member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee. 
  Accompanied by Gao Dezhan, secretary of the Tianjin 
Municipal 
Committee of the CPC, and Zhang Lichang, mayor of Tianjin, Hu 
Jintao inspected a number of villages and rural industrial 
enterprises. 
  He discussed with officials at county, township and village 
levels how to further strengthen building of the CPC grassroots 
organizations in the rural areas. 
  He also visited some farm produce markets, grain shops and 
large and medium-sized enterprises and talked with workers and 
local residents, inquiring about the situation of their work and 
daily life and gathering their opinions and suggestions. 
  During his tour of inspection, he stressed the need to 
further strengthen the building up of the party. 
  In the countryside, he said, it was necessary to make great 
efforts to establish strong village party branches, promote to 
the position of the party branch secretary those party members 
who are of good political quality, willing to serve the people, 
good at business and management, and able to lead the local 
people to develop the economy. 

</TEXT>

