<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Henan Province To Build Large Gas Network </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Henan Province To Build Large Gas Network </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2506021294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0156 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2506021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zhengzhou, June 25 (XINHUA) -- China's major coal 
producer, Henan Province, plans to invest 1.84 billion yuan 
(about 220 million U.S. dollars) in the construction of a large 
gasification network. 
  The project, approved by the State Council, is scheduled to 
start late next year and be completed in three years. 
  The network will be centered in Yima city, a key coal 
production base in the province. It will consist of a 
gasification plant and a pipeline network. 
  Pithead coal gasification plants will be built at the Yima 
coal mines. 
  The first phase of the construction will be aimed at 
producing 1.2 million cu m of coal gas a day, 290,000 cu m of 
which will be used to make petrochemical products and the rest 
supplied to Luoyang and Zhengzhou cities for household use. 
  The second phase aims at a daily output of 2.4 million cu m 
of gas to ensure supplies to the other key cities of Kaifeng, 
Sanmenxia, Xuchang and Xinxiang. 
  Local officials predict that the construction of the network 
will also help improve pollution control and spur local economic 
development. 
  The province plans to use foreign funds and import advanced 
technologies and equipment from other countries for the project. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-26726 </DOCNO>
