<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hubei Hosts Development Symposium 18-19 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hubei Hosts Development Symposium 18-19 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2506043694 Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
1000 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2506043694 </F>
<F P=104>  Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Central China Development Symposium was held in 
Wuhan from 18 to 19 June. 
  The symposium was attended by representatives from several 
Central China provinces; Chen Yaobang, State Planning Commission 
vice minister; and Wang Shengtie, provincial party committee 
standing committee member and provincial vice governor. 
  Chen Yaobang and Wang Shengtie delivered speeches at the 
symposium. 
  The symposium concluded: Central China possesses boundless 
economic development potential. 
  At the symposium, representatives from Hunan Province, Hubei 
Province, Henan Province, Anhui Province, Jiangxi Province, and 
Wuhan City joined economic experts from the State Council 
Development Research Center, the Chang Jiang Water Conservancy 
Commission, the State Planning Commission, and other state 
departments concerned in exploring and discussing a new Central 
China development strategy. 
  The symposium participants held: The five Central China 
provinces have always been China's key agricultural commodities 
production bases and have been rich in energy resources, raw and 
processed goods and materials, labor resources, and advanced and 
convenient communications systems as well, thus being of 
strategic importance to the country's economic development. 
Exploitation and opening up of Central China will be an 
inevitable result of China's coastal opening up. The 
exploitation and opening up of Central China will not only 
provide the country's industrialization with an important 
guarantee but also promote rejuvenation and development of the 
country's hinterland, thereby enhancing the country's national 
economic reserve strength. 
  The symposium participants maintained: Located in the middle 
and lower reaches of the Chang Jiang and along the Chang Jiang, 
Hubei should strive to firmly seize the excellent opportunity at 
the moment to learn from Shanghai's Pudong by simultaneously 
opening up to the outside world and domestic regions and 
simultaneously making full use of foreign and domestic 
resources; open up more overseas and domestic markets; 
expeditiously carry out multilevel, multichannel, and 
omnidirectional opening up; encourage areas where conditions 
allow to develop faster and relatively prosperous areas to 
assist relatively backward areas; bring into full play the 
radiation role of each and every key city and key development 
zone; energetically develop a regional economy; speed up 
regional industrial structural readjustment; and further improve 
regional economic quality with an eye to pressing ahead with the 
economic development of the entire Chang Jiang Valley. 
  The symposium also disclosed: The state will this year draw 
up a regional economic development plan aimed at boosting the 
economic development of Hubei Province, Henan Province, Hunan 
Province, Jiangxi Province, and Anhui Province. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

