<F P=102>   OW2506165094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1525 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2506165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 25 (XINHUA) -- Huaxia Township 
Enterprise Institute, the first college in China with 
share-holders, was inaugurated at the Zhejiang Agricultural 
University here today. 
  The institute was set up jointly by the Township Enterprise 
Department of the Ministry of Agriculture, the Township 
Enterprise Bureau of the Zhejiang Provincial Government and 
Zhejiang Agricultural University. It is to train technical 
personnel for rural industrial enterprises. 
  He Kang, former minister of agriculture, was elected 
honorary 
chairman of the board of the institute. Liu Xirong, 
vice-governor of Zhejiang Province, was elected honorary 
president. 
  Xu Xingguan, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of 
Zhejiang Provincial People's Congress, was elected chairman of 
the board. 

