<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official on Changes to Corporate Registration System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official on Changes to Corporate Registration System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2606221594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1112 
GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2606221594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Fu Gang (0265 0474)] </F>
  [Text] Hohhot, 21 Jun (XINHUA) -- Cao Tiandian, director of 
the State Administration for Industry and Commerce, said today 
at the National Work Conference on the Management of Enterprise 
Registration that the system of company registration would be 
drastically adjusted in conjunction with the formal 
implementation of the "Company Law of the People's Republic of 
China" on 1 July. 
  With the enforcement of the "Company Law," the direction of 
China's enterprise reform will shift from a mere granting of 
more power to enterprises to that of a systematic change, or to 
establishing a modern enterprise system. Straightening out 
property rights relationships and defining the corporate 
property rights of enterprises are at the center of this system. 
The corporate system will be adopted as the major form of 
promoting the system. 
  To achieve that end, the company registration system will 
make a break with the former ownership registration system; 
instead it will emphasize enterprise property. For instance, 
registered capital (fund provider uses this to undertake 
company's limited liability) will replace registered funds (no 
stipulation on undertaking what kind of responsibility toward 
the company) to reflect in a timely manner corporate property 
rights. The new system will merge operational methods and 
scopes into one and term them operational scope to realize the 
granting of autonomous operation rights to enterprises. 
Starting from the day of the implementation of the "Company 
Law," and excluding stipulations provided for separately in the 
state laws and administrative regulations, the fund provider 
shall directly apply for registration with the administrative 
organs for industry and commerce; thus scrapping the examination 
and approval by competent administrative departments. Local 
laws and provisions, administrative rules, and other documents 
relating to trade and commerce management departments' special 
examination and approval will cease to be the prerequisite 
conditions for registration. 
  Cao Tiandian said the State Council will soon promulgate 
"Regulations on Management of Enterprise Registration of the 
People's Republic of China." The "regulations," he said, will 
provide specific stipulations to the principles set down in the 
"Company Law." He added that the pace of drafting a number of 
documents to complement the "Company Law" has been accelerated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-26742 </DOCNO>
