<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Police Force Commander Inspects Heilongjiang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Police Force Commander Inspects Heilongjiang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2306123994 Harbin HEILONGJIANG RIBAO in Chinese 15 Jun 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> SK2306123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin HEILONGJIANG RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yue Qifeng, secretary of the provincial party 
committee, went to the headquarters of the provincial people's 
armed police force to call on Lieutenant General Ba Zhongtan, 
commander of Chinese People's Armed Police Force, and his 
entourage on the afternoon of 14 June, who were making an 
inspection tour in the province. 
  During the visit, Yue Qifeng spoke highly of the 
achievements scored by the provincial people's armed police 
force since its founding. Ba Zhongtan extended heartfelt thanks 
for the concern and support given to the people's armed police 
force by the provincial party committee and the provincial 
people's government. 
  Commander Ba Zhongtan and his entourage arrived in Harbin on 
the morning of 13 June. 
  On the afternoon of 13 June Shan Rongfan, deputy secretary 
of 
the provincial party committee; Xu Yandong, assistant to 
governor; and leading personnel from the provincial public 
security department; went to the Huayuancun Hotel to call on 
Commander Ba Zhongtan and his entourage. 
  During their stay in Harbin, Ba Zhongtan and his entourage 
inspected the fifth armed police force detachment, which is in 
charge of mobile units. They paid tribute to the strict 
management, assiduous training, and rapid reaction of the 
detachment. During the forum with the police officers and 
fighters, Commander Ba Zhongtan repeatedly urged them to 
enhance their study; to safeguard stability; and to become loyal 
guards who are cherished by the people and feared by enemies. 

</TEXT>

