<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wen Jiabao Inspects Flood Situation in Jiangxi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wen Jiabao Inspects Flood Situation in Jiangxi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2506172894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1632 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2506172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By JIANGXI RIBAO reporter Zhang Wei (1728 3555) and XINHUA </F>
reporter Wu Huaguo (0702 5478 0948)] 
  [Text] Nanchang, 24 Jun (XINHUA) -- A central work team led 
Wen Jiabao, alternate member of the CPC Central Committee 
Political Bureau and member of the CPC Central Committee 
Secretariat, arrived in Jiangxi from Hunan this morning to 
provide on-the-spot guideance for Jiangxi to conduct 
flood-fighting and relief work and to resume industrial and 
agricultural production. 
  Immediately after disembarking from the plane, Wen Jiabao 
and 
his party -- accompanied by Mao Zhiyong, secretary of the 
Jiangxi Provincial Party Committee, and Governor Wu Guanzheng -- 
successively rushed to the Nanchang Bridge, the Leigongao 
construction work site along the Nanchang-Jiujiang Highway which 
is reserved for vehicles, Weidong Village under Changling Town 
in Xinjian County, and Houtian Township's Sanzhou Village. They 
inspected the flood situation along the Ganjiang River, visited 
the masses of flood victims, and extended greetings and 
appreciation to the servicemembers and civilians who have been 
performing rescue and emergency tasks. The same evening, Wen 
Jiabao and his party earnestly listened to reports by the 
Jiangxi Provincial Party Committee and government on Jiangxi's 
flood situation and its flood-fighting and relief work. 
  Wen Jiabao highly commended Jiangxi's servicemembers and 
people for their spirit that stresses fostering unity and 
coordinated efforts, striving to help and rescue themselves, and 
continually fighting when encountering extraordinarily 
disastrous floods. He also fully affirmed Jiangxi's preliminary 
victories in its flood-fighting and relief work. Wen Jiabao 
pointed out: At present, the Ganjiang River's water-level is 
declining, but the Jiangxi Provincial Party Committee and 
government are still facing very arduous tasks. While 
continually and properly conducting flood-fighting and relief 
work along the Ganjiang River valleys, we should stress 
flood-prevention in the Poyang Lake area and should promptly 
organize the masses in the disaster-stricken areas to resume 
production so as to be self-reliant and to rebuild their homes. 
Jiangxi is a major agricultural province. We should take 
measures to promptly salvage the early-ripening rice, and should 
expand the planting of late-ripening rice and autumn grain as 
much as possible so as to attain a bumper harvest of grain for 
the whole year. While carrying out flood-fighting and relief 
work, we should also continually and properly handle various 
tasks concerning reform, stability, and development in Jiangxi. 
  It has been learned that on 25 June Wen Jiabao and his party 
will visit other localities including Xingan, Fengcheng, and 
Jian where the flooding has been the most serious. They will 
further inspect the flood situation and extend sympathy and 
solicitude to flood victims there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-26769 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi123_k_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-123 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  26 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wen Jiabao, Spokesman Comment on Flood Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wen Jiabao, Spokesman Comment on Flood Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2606142694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1401 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2606142694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 26 (XINHUA) -- Floods have all 
receded along Xijiang, Beijiang, Xiangjiang and Ganjiang except 
at a section of the Xijiang River in Wuzhou city, Guangxi, a 
spokesman from the State Flood Control and Drought Relief 
Headquarters announced today. 
  The spokesman attributed the falling water level to the 
major 
water conservancy projects which help to mitigate losses. 
Meanwhile, he said, tension has been eased in the Pearl River 
delta as the latest tropical storm has been weakened after 
landing in Yangjiang city, Guangdong Province. 
  Floods hit Guangdong, Guangxi, Hunan, Jiangxi, Fujiang and 
Zhejiang provinces following the first heavy rains and floods 
which typically hit China from the south to the north from June 
to August. 
  Earlier reports said that successive torrential rainstorms 
in 
the Xijiang and Beijiang river valleys in early and mid-June 
resulted in a big flood, one of the most serious in 100 years, 
in Guangdong Province and caused heavy losses. Major flood 
monitoring stations on the two rivers recorded their highest 
water levels, all four meters above the warning level. 
  In an urgent conference late yesterday, the Guangdong 
provincial government urged localities to help flood victims 
with food, shelter, clothing and medical care so that no one 
would die of hunger and no epidemic disease would break out in 
the flooded areas. 
  The province has allocated 300 million kg of grain and 110 
million yuan in cash along with over 10 million tons of such 
farm production supplies as chemical fertilizer and diesel oil 
to the flood-stricken areas. 
  Meanwhile, 740 million yuan in loans and another 50 million 
yuan in donations have also been sent to flooded areas in 
Guangdong Province. 
  While inspecting flood control and relief work in Jiangxi 
Province, through which the Ganjiang flows, Wen Jiabao, 
alternate member of the Political Bureau and member of the 
Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee, said the flooded areas 
should work hard to mitigate losses through their own efforts 
and with support from various departments. 
  While inspecting Nanchang, the capital city of Jiangxi, and 
Fengcheng, Xingang, Jian and Taihe, on June 24-26, Wen said the 
key to mitigating economic losses is to resume production as 
soon as possible. 
  The localities should waste no time in implementing various 
measures to resume production and rehabilitate their homeland, 
he said. 
  As one of China's major bread baskets, Jiangxi is of key 
importance to China in agricultural production, Wen said. It 
has a direct bearing on the grain supply in south China. He 
urged the local governments to farmers resume agricultural 
production. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-26770 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi123_k_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-123 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wen Jiabao Inspects Hunan Flood Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wen Jiabao Inspects Hunan Flood Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2406144294 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1429 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2406144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Shi Tao (4258 3447)] </F>
  [Text] Changsha, 23 Jun (XINHUA) -- Speaking in Hunan where 
he was directing the work of combating flood and doing disaster 
relief, Wen Jiabao, alternate member of the CPC Central 
Committee Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat, 
pointed out: To successfully carry out the work of combating 
flood and disaster relief, we must rely on the masses, rely on 
ourselves, work hard, rely on unity between the military and 
civilians, and rely on strong leadership of the party and 
government. Party committees and governments at all levels in 
the disaster area should regard the work of fighting disaster 
and carrying out disaster relief their central task of paramount 
importance at the present stage and should meticulously organize 
the efforts, make overall consideration and all-round 
arrangement, and make an all-out effort to carry out flood 
prevention and disaster relief and to engage in production to 
provide for and help ourselves. 
  From 21 to 23 June, Wen Jiabao led a work group of 
responsible comrades of central party, Army, and government 
departments concerned to the great dike along the Xiangshui and 
to several major disaster areas in Hunan's Changsha, Zhuzhou, 
Xiangtan, and Hengyang, where they inspected the disaster 
situation. On behalf of the party Central Committee, the State 
Council, and the Central Military Commission, they extended 
cordial regards to flood victims as well as to cadres, the 
masses, People's Liberation Army [PLA] commanders and fighters, 
armed police, and public security cadres and officers. Together 
with the local party and government leaders, they studied and 
arranged for flood prevention and disaster relief work. 
  Heavy rainstorm hit areas along the Xiangshui from 12 to 18 
June, creating great flood unseen in 100 years and causing heavy 
losses to industrial and agricultural production and to people's 
lives and property in urban and rural areas along the river. 
After the outbreak of the disaster, under the leadership of the 
Hunan provincial party committee and government and with the 
support of the PLA and armed police units in Hunan, the military 
and civilians in the province spared no efforts in fighting the 
disaster. Their efforts have ensured the safety of Changsha, 
Zhuzhou, Xiangtan, Hengyang Cities, as well as the 
Beijing-Guangzhou Railway, State Highway 107, and other major 
transportation facilities; reduced losses caused by the 
disaster; and scored initial success in combating flood and 
carrying out disaster relief. At present, the masses in the 
disaster area are calm in their sentiments, society is stable, 
and life is normal. 
  Wen Jiabao fully affirmed Hunan's fight against flood and 
its 
disaster relief work. He urged the military and civilians 
throughout the province to display the dauntless spirit of 
fighting successive battles to win all-around victories in 
fighting the disaster and carrying out relief. 
  After hearing a report on the disaster and observing the 
disaster situation, Wen Jiabao also expressed his views on the 
work of fighting the disaster and carrying out relief. He said: 
The Xiangshui's water level is subsiding. However, its flood 
season has not arrived yet. We must not lower our guard and 
become careless; we must continue to do a good job of preparing 
against big flood and disaster. First, we must step up 
repairing various works damaged by water and reinforcing the 
dike. This is the key to preventing flood. Second, we must 
make adequate arrangement for the victims' daily life, properly 
resolve their food and clothing problems, and carry out public 
health and epidemic prevention work. Third, we must organize 
efforts to provide for and help ourselves and to rebuild our 
homes by engaging in production, and we must restore industrial 
and agricultural production. Fourth, we must strengthen 
ideological-political work to further mobilize the initiatives 
of the vast number of cadres and masses in fighting the disaster 
and carrying out disaster relief. Fifth, we must strengthen 
leadership. Party committees and governments in disaster areas 
must lead the broad masses to rely on themselves and rebuild 
their homeland through thrift and diligence. All departments 
should work closely and provide big support to overcome various 
difficulties. We must unite as one to fight the disaster and 
carry out disaster relief. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

