<H3> <TI>   Beijing, Tripoli Discuss Economic, Scientific Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing, Tripoli Discuss Economic, Scientific Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2706083094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0758 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2706083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 27 (XINHUA) -- The fifth meeting of 
the Sino-Libyan Mixed Committee for Economic, Trade, Scientific 
and Technological Cooperation opened here this morning. 
  Wu Yi, China's minister of foreign trade and economic 
cooperation, and Fathi Bin-Shatwan, Libya's secretary for 
industry and mineral resources, presided over the opening 
ceremony. 
  Wu said that China is keen on developing trade and economic 
relations with Libya, and recent years had seen a smooth growth 
of these relations. 
  "We hope to further the relations considering the strong 
complementary nature of the two economies." 
  Bin-Shatwan said Libyan-Chinese economic and trade relations 
had developed quickly with great potential since the mixed 
committee was formed in 1982. 
  He hoped that China would get to know the Libyan market 
better and get further involved in Libya's economic development. 

</TEXT>

