<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Cites Burmese Official on Eliminating Drug Abuse </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    111 Operations Against Warlord Khun Sa </H4>

<F P=102> OW2606150094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1436 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2606150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yangon [Rangoon], June 26 (XINHUA) -- Myanmar 
[Burma] Government armed forces conducted 111 operations against 
drug warlord Khun Sa's armed group in Shan State, eastern 
Myanmar, from May 11 to June 24, the official radio reported 
here tonight. 
  During the battles, 196 Myanmar armymen were killed, other 
375 were wounded, according to the report. 
  The report also said that the government army found 250 dead 
bodies of the Khun Sa armed group, and seized a lot of arms and 
ammunition. 
  Khun Sa is a drug warlord in the notorious golden triangle 
region which borders Myanmar, Laos and Thailand. 

</TEXT>

