<H3> <TI>   Thai Delegations To Visit Mideast, China, U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Thai Delegations To Visit Mideast, China, U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2706032894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0304 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2706032894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, June 27 (XINHUA) -- Three delegations of 
both government and the private sectors will visit the Middle 
East, the United States and China from the end of June to July 
in an effort to extend trade and investment cooperation. 
  The trips will provide the private sector an opportunity to 
exchange views and information with those countries, according 
to a statement of Foreign Ministry available here today. 
  On June 26-July 3, Deputy Permanent Secretary Pradyatawee 
Tavedikul will lead a group of private businessmen to Kuwait, 
Bahrain and the United Arab Emirates to explore business 
opportunities in the fields of telecommunication, aviation, 
labor, and stock exchanges. 
  Deputy Director-General of the Economics Department Chaiyong 
Sajjipanon, in cooperation with the Thai Chamber of Commerce, 
left for southern China on Sunday [26 June] with a private 
sector delegation to analyze the consumer goods, real estate 
and hotel industries. 
  Economics Department Chief Sukhum Rasameethat will lead 
another delegation to Israel and the United States to explore 
the jewelery market on July 15-29. 

