<H3> <TI>   Japanese Newspaper Office Attacked by Ultra-Rightist </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese Newspaper Office Attacked by Ultra-Rightist </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2606085794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0815 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2606085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 26 (XINHUA) -- A loudspeaker truck 
driven by a member of an illegal ultra-rightist group hit the 
front door of the office building of the ASAHI SHIMBUN newspaper 
in Osaka on Saturday [25 June], causing no casualty, local media 
reported today. 
  The truck smashed the windows of the front door of the 
building after hitting it twice. The driver, a member of a 
local illegal ultra-rightist group, was arrested by police for 
"object destruction offenses." 
  A lot of Japanese ultra-rightist groups, including the one 
involved this time, are connected with organized criminal groups 
and other violence groups. 
  This is the fourth time for ASAHI SHIMBUN to be attacked by 
ultra-rightist groups since April 1, when two of its staff 
members were taken hostage by members of a Tokyo ultra-rightist 
group in the newspaper's headquarters in Tokyo. 
  On April 21, the newspaper's Osaka office building was 
attacked by an ultra-rightist loudspeaker truck smashing its way 
into the building. 
  On April 25, the building was attacked with firebombs by 
ultra-rights. 

</TEXT>

