<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Says Russian-EU Pact of `Historic Importance' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Says Russian-EU Pact of `Historic Importance' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Represents Economic `Comeback' Step </H4>

<F P=102> OW2406135994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1320 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2406135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Athens, June 24 (XINHUA) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin said here today that the Russian-EU partnership 
agreement is of "historic importance" and represents the first 
step of Russia's economic comeback to Europe. 
  Speaking after signing the pact at the European Union 
summit, 
Yeltsin said the agreement marks the end of ideological and 
economic conflicts that prevailed during the Cold War era. 
  "We all felt the symptoms of an economic Cold War, but this 
threat is being abolished with this agreement," said Yeltsin. 
"Today, Russia becomes a significant partner of the Europeans, 
and we will do everything possible to support European 
integration." 
  He added that Moscow would back efforts aimed at enlarging 
the 12-nation bloc, which will extend formal membership to four 
countries later today. 

</TEXT>

