<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Sun Weiben Meets With Tajik Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Heilongjiang Sun Weiben Meets With Tajik Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2506045594 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2200 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2506045594 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Supreme Soviet delegation of the Republic of 
Tajikistan, headed by First Deputy Prime Minister Dostiyev, paid 
a visit to the provincial people's congress standing committee 
on the morning of 24 June. 
  Sun Weiben, chairman of the provincial people's congress 
standing committee, met with dostiyev and his party. On behalf 
of the provincial people's congress standing committee, Sun 
Weiben expressed his warm welcome to the delegation. 
  He said that the delegation's visit will lay a good 
foundation for establishing friendly contacts and economic and 
trade cooperation ties between Heilongjiang Province and 
Tajikistan. 
  Sun Weiben introduced to the guests the province's political 
and economic situation. 
  He said: Tajikistan and Heilongjiang are economically 
complementary. Thus, both sides have great potentials for 
developing economic and trade cooperation. I hope that both 
sides will be able to strengthen contacts, enhance mutual 
understanding, and promote cooperation. 
  dostiyev thanked the provincial people's congress for its 
cordial reception. 
  He said: The people in Tajikistan cherish a deep affection 
for the Chinese people. So, we should strengthen cooperation 
and make common development. 
  Qi Guiyuan, Du Xianzhong, Du Dianming, and Liu Hanwu, vice 
chairman of the provincial people's congress standing committee; 
and Liu Fengyan, secretary general of the provincial people's 
congress standing committee, were present at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

