BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, June 24 (XINHUA) -- The Supreme Allied 
Commander, Europe (Saceur), General George A. Joulwan, will 
visit Russia on June 26-28 at the invitation of Russia's first 
deputy defense minister, General Mikhail Petrovich Kolesnikov. 
  A NATO spokesman said that the visit demonstrates the great 
value that both Russia and NATO attach to an intensification of 
military contacts. 
  During his visit, General Joulwan will meet the Russian 
Minister of Defense General Pavel Grachev, and General 
Kolesnikov, to exchange views on issues of mutual interest. 
  He will also lay a wreath at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier 
in Moscow and visit an operational military unit, the 27th 
Motorized Rifle Brigade. 
  On Wednesday [22 June] Russia signed a framework document 
for 
the "partnership for peace" program with NATO. 

