<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports Progress on Airport Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Reports Progress on Airport Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2406151694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1503 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2406151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, June 24 (XINHUA) -- The airport committee 
of the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG) ended its meeting 
here this afternoon with both sides having claimed that further 
progress has been made over the airport issue. 
  "We have discussed the issue of the financial arrangements 
in 
today's airport committee meeting and have made further progress 
over the issue," said Guo Fengmin, senior representative of the 
Chinese team of the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group. 
  "We have decided to entrust the experts to draw up a 
document 
of the meeting, which will be signed by the senior 
representatives of the two sides as an agreement of both sides," 
he said. 
  "Of course, we still need to study some of the details and 
wording in the document, we hope to complete the drafting of the 
document as soon as possible," he said, adding that the progress 
achieved between China and Britain is the result of the common 
efforts of both sides. 
  Hugh Davies, senior representative to the British side of 
the 
JLG confirmed the progress as guo claimed in a press briefing 
given after the meeting. 
  "We are still discussing some of the details," he said, 
adding that he was confident that an agreement over the airport 
issue would be reached on the basis of the progress that the two 
sides had made. 

</TEXT>

