<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hefei, June 25 (XINHUA) -- Hefei, capital of east 
China's Anhui Province, had approved the establishment of 727 
new foreign-funded enterprises by the end of May this year. 
  According to local officials, these enterprises have 
promised 
to invest a total of 520 million U.S. dollars, accounting for 
one third of the province's total foreign investment. 
  The officials said the distribution of foreign investment in 
the city has changed from solely industry oriented and become 
relatively harmonized, with its proportion in agriculture 
standing for two percent, in industry 68 percent and in the 
