<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice Premier Li Lanqing Meets Directors of New Bank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Premier Li Lanqing Meets Directors of New Bank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2406145894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1443 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2406145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 24 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li 
Lanqing had a meeting here today with the full board of 
directors of the recently-created Import and Export Bank of 
China (CEIB). 
  He stressed the need to give the utmost help to promote 
China's exports, particularly of machinery, electronics and 
other equipment. 
  CEIB is China's second policy bank after the People's Bank 
of 
China, the central bank. Established in Beijing on April 27 
this year, the bank is responsible for providing import and 
export credits for capital goods, including large machinery and 
electronic equipment. 
  It also handles credits as well as government and commercial 
loans provided by foreign countries for their import of Chinese 
capital goods. 
  Vice-Premier Li recalled that the bank was set up to meet 
the 
needs of establishing a socialist market economic system, speed 
up the reform of the financial system, separate the policy 
banking business from commercial banking business, enable the 
country's foreign trade to develop in a sustained, steady and 
healthy way, improve the structure, grade and quality of export 
commodities, and increase exports. 
  Vice-Premier Li urged the CEIB to formulate strict rules and 
regulations and establish a strict internal management system. 

</TEXT>

