<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Luo Gan Arrives in Tripoli 25 Jun on 4-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Luo Gan Arrives in Tripoli 25 Jun on 4-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Talks on Ties, Mutual Interests </H4>

<F P=102> OW2506165594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1635 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2506165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, June 25 (XINHUA) -- Chinese State 
Councillor and Secretary General of the State Council Luo Gan 
arrived here this afternoon for a four-day friendly visit to 
Libya at the invitation of the General People's Committee 
(cabinet). 
  Upon his arrival, Luo Gan was received by 'Umar Mustafa 
al-Muntasir, secretary for foreign liaison and international 
cooperation (foreign minister) of Libya's General People's 
Committee. 
  In a written statement issued on his arrival in Tripoli, Luo 
Gan said that China and Libya are two countries linked together 
by friendly ties, and that the ties of friendship and 
cooperation between them have developed satisfactorily since 
they established diplomatic relations in 1978. 
  He said that during his current visit to Libya he would meet 
with Libyan leaders and have talks with the 'Umar Mustafa 
al-Muntasir on bilateral ties between the two countries as well 
as international and regional issues of mutual interest. 
  Luo expressed confidence that his current visit to Libya 
would contribute to consolidating friendship and understanding 
between the Chinese and Libyan peoples and would promote the 
existing cooperation between the two countries. 
  The Chinese official arrived here by road from Tunis after 
visiting Tunisia. 

</TEXT>

