<F P=103> OW2806042494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 28 (XINHUA) -- Negotiators from the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and South Korea met 
today at the truce village of Panmunjom, starting the talks in 
preparations for a inter-Korean summit. 
  If successful, the talks will set a time and place of the 
summit between DPRK President Kim Il-song and South Korean 
President Kim Yong-sam. 
  The DPRK's delegation was headed by Kim Yong-son, chairman 
of 
