<H3> <TI>   Ford Launches Its First Joint Venture in Country </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ford Launches Its First Joint Venture in Country </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2706131494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1301 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2706131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, June 27 (XINHUA) -- Ford Motor Company of 
the United States signed agreements with two Chinese enterprises 
here today to establish two joint ventures producing auto 
components. 
  These are the first Ford-launched manufacturing companies in 
China. 
  According to the agreements signed today, Ford and the 
Yanfeng division of the Shanghai Automotive Industry Corporation 
will set up a company to manufacture plastic automotive 
components, including interior trim, seats, instrument panels 
and other plastic parts for the Chinese auto industry. 
  The joint venture between Ford and Shanghai Yaohua Glass 
Works will produce auto safety glass and architectural glass. 
  "For Ford Motor Company, these new partnerships represent 
the 
beginning of our manufacturing presence in China, this important 
new market, and the chance to show our strength and commitment," 
said James Paulsen, president of Ford China Operations. 
  Ford will invest more than 50 million U.S. dollars in all in 
these two projects. 

</TEXT>

